The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 12, 2004 				 Group pension scheme
																								Dubai, Aug. 11: Aviva Life Insurance today launched its group superannuation product for the organised sector. 																								The plan is essentially a defined contribution unit-linked plan, designed primarily to enable companies provide pension benefits to their employees at the time of retirement.																								The employer can make a contribution of up to 15 per cent of basic salary of the employee towards this fund. The employee is also entitled to make voluntary contributions into the superannuation fund.																								The product offers five fund options of cash, debt, secure, balanced and growth with an option to switch twice from one fund to the other in a year. 
